he toxicity of CMNs, particularly to support their practical application in medical fields. Fundamental molecular assays and detailed investigations into the mechanisms of action of CMNs are also needed to better understand their efficacy and potential side effects. Furthermore, the standardisation of CMN processing protocols is crucial, especially considering their prospective use in pharmaceuticals and even functional foods, to ensure both effectiveness and product safety. Publisher’s note Springer Nature remains neutral with regard to jurisdictional claims in published maps and institutional affiliations. Rahmat Budiarto and Mohammad Miftakhus Sholikin have contributed equally to this work. Acknowledgements The authors would like to express their sincere appreciation to Universitas Padjadjaran, Indonesia for supporting this work through the Article Processing Charge Assistance Program for the 2025 fiscal year. Author contributions R.B.: conceptualization, supervision, funding acquisition, writing the original draft, and writing the review and editing. M.M.S and T.U.: conceptualization, supervision, visualization, writing the original draft, and writing the review and editing. D.N.A.: project administration, validation, writing the original draft, and writing the review and editing. T.W.: data curation, formal analysis, writing the original draft, and writing the review and editing. T.A. and H.M.A: investigation, data curation, writing the review and editing. Funding Open access funding provided by University of Padjadjaran. This work was funded by Universitas Padjadjaran, Indonesia. Data availability The datasets used and/or analysed during the current study available from the corresponding author on reasonable request. Declarations Competing interests The authors declare no competing interests. Ethical approval This research is an original study that has not been submitted or published elsewhere. It utilizes secondary data sourced from previous research and does